[{"id":"VR023904","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VR023901.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following will the firm do in the long run if market conditions do not change?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR023904_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<p class=\"lead_in\">The following two questions refer to the cost and revenue conditions of a monopolistically competitive firm shown in the graph below.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"A line graph plots dollars against quantity. Points Q 1 through Q 3 are marked on the horizontal axis. Points P 1 through P 5 are marked on the vertical axis. The graph displays five curves, namely, M C, A T C, A V C, demand, and M R. Both the A T C and A V C curves are concave up curves. The A T C curve lies above the A V C curve.  When the price increases from P 1 to P 3, there will be a greater supply in quantity. That is, the quantity supplied increases from Q 1 to Q 3. This is represented by dashed lines connecting P 1 and Q 1, P 2 and Q 2, and P 3 and Q 3. The dashed line from Q 1 connects P 4. A line labeled M C increases linearly, moving through the intersection points of the dashed lines connecting P 1 Q 1, P 2 Q 2, and P 3 Q 3, and intersects the A T C and A V C curves at their minimum points. Lines representing demand and M R start from the same point P 5 on the vertical axis, decrease sharply, moving through the intersection points of the dashed lines P 1 Q 1 and P 2 Q 2.\" height=\"346\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR023901.g03.png\" width=\"300\" /></div>\n\n<div class=\"passage\">\n<div class=\"prose style:1\">\n<p class=\"passage_para\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Uppercase M C equals \"><math overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mstyle> <mrow> <mtext>MC =</mtext> </mrow> </mstyle> </math></span></span> marginal cost, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Uppercase A T C equals\"><math overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mstyle> <mrow> <mtext>ATC =</mtext> </mrow> </mstyle> </math></span></span> average total cost, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Uppercase A V C equals\"><math overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mstyle> <mrow> <mtext>AVC =</mtext> </mrow> </mstyle> </math></span></span>average variable cost, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Uppercase M R equals\"><math overflow=\"scroll\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mstyle> <mrow> <mtext>MR =</mtext> </mrow> </mstyle> </math></span></span> marginal revenue.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It will increase output to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 2\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and lower price to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 2\"><math alttext=\"P sub 2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>P</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to minimize losses.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It will increase output to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 3\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 3\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and raise price to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"P sub 4\"><math alttext=\"P sub 4\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>P</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to earn zero economic profit.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It will produce <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Q sub 1\"><math alttext=\"Q sub 1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mtext>Q</mtext></mrow><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> and set price equal to marginal revenue.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It will exit the industry.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">It will build a larger plant to achieve decreasing returns to scale.</p>"],"answer":3}]